Using searchingforstrangeness
=============================

Copyright (C) searchingforstrangeness contributors.

This file describes normal use of the package after it has been checked out and
built inside a MicroBooNE ubana development area.  For installation and build
instructions, see INSTALL.  For a repository overview, see README.  For
dataset naming and SAM-definition notes, see scripts/README.md.


Conventions
-----------

The examples below assume:

  * you are running from the top of this repository;
  * the package has already been built in a working MRB area;
  * the MicroBooNE software environment is active;
  * your input files are art ROOT files from the expected reconstruction chain.

Several checked-in FHiCL files use relative paths such as "runtime" and
"scripts/inference_wrapper.sh".  Running from the repository top directory is
the simplest way to make those paths resolve as expected.


1. Prepare the runtime environment
----------------------------------

Complete the setup and build steps in INSTALL first.

For interactive work from this checkout, the usual sequence is:

     ./.container.sh
     source .setup.sh

If your shell is already in the correct MicroBooNE/MRB environment, sourcing
.setup.sh from the repository top directory is usually enough.  That helper
also sets up sam_web_client for the SAM-based workflows described below.

For SAM write operations on the GPVM such as `samweb create-definition`, a
stale bearer-token environment can cause confusing auth failures.  The working
recovery sequence from this checkout was:

     unset BEARER_TOKEN
     unset BEARER_TOKEN_FILE
     htdestroytoken || true
     htgettoken -a htvaultprod.fnal.gov -i uboone

After that, `samweb create-definition ...` succeeded without needing an
explicit `BEARER_TOKEN_FILE` export.


2. Choose a checked-in job configuration
----------------------------------------

The standard entry points are under jobs/.

jobs/run_nuselection.fcl
     Runs the neutrino-selection filter on MC-style input and writes the
     analysis TTree file nu_selection.root.

jobs/run_nuselection_data.fcl
     Runs the data/EXT version of the selection and writes
     nu_selection_data.root.

jobs/run_nuselection_slim.fcl
     Runs the MC-style selection on input that already contains imageprod
     products, but skips loading inference products.  It writes
     nu_selection_slim.root.

jobs/run_nuselection_data_slim.fcl
     Runs the data/EXT selection on input that already contains imageprod
     products, but skips loading inference products.  It writes
     nu_selection_data_slim.root.

jobs/run_nuselection_slim_oldflux_rw.fcl
     Runs the slim MC-style selection on old-flux-reweighted input and writes
     nu_selection_slim_oldflux_rw.root.

jobs/run_imageprod.fcl
     Produces image::ImageFeatures objects for the selected slice and a
     full-detector companion collection, then writes the event file
     %ifb_%tc_imageprod.root.  The checked-in TFileService output is
     imageprod_hist.root.

jobs/run_inferenceprod.fcl
     Runs model inference on existing imageprod:CroppedWindow products and writes
     the event file %ifb_%tc_inference.root.  The checked-in TFileService
     output is inferenceprod_hist.root.

jobs/run_fullchain.fcl
     Runs image production, inference, and neutrino selection in one process.
     It writes %ifb_%tc_fullchain_nuselection.root and
     fullchain_nuselection_hist.root.

jobs/run_fullchain_slim.fcl
     Runs the slim redk2nu, EventWeight, image, and neutrino-selection chain
     in one process.

jobs/run_fullchain_slim_oldflux_rw.fcl
     Old-flux-reweighted counterpart to the slim fullchain wrapper.

run_redk2nu_fhc.fcl
run_redk2nu_rhc.fcl
     Restore Dk2Nu information to reco2 artroot files before EventWeight,
     using the FHC or RHC NuMI dk2nu file paths from the sibling ubana
     redk2nu package.

The development entry points are under jobs/dev/.

jobs/dev/flux/run_imageprod_dev.fcl
     Development chain for imaging, inference, and selection with event-weight
     analysis enabled.

jobs/dev/flux/run_imageprod_oldflux_rw_dev.fcl
     Old-flux variant of the same imaging, inference, and selection chain.

jobs/dev/run_imageprod_data_dev.fcl
     Development chain for cosmic/data-style imaging and selection studies.

jobs/dev/run_stage_sel_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for the staged MC-style selection step.

jobs/dev/run_stage_fullchain_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for running the image, inference, and selection chain in
     one process while still using dev-local output names.

jobs/dev/flux/run_local_ntuple_dev.fcl
     Local MC-style ntuple job for downstream ntuple validation.  It runs the
     redk2nu, eventweight, and image stages in-process, writes the
     EventSelectionFilter and SubRun trees, keeps only 100 GENIE and 100 PPFX
     universes, uses the standard NuMI EventWeight chain, and leaves
     inference disabled until the checked-in model bundle is refreshed.

jobs/dev/flux/run_local_ntuple_oldflux_dev.fcl
     Old-flux counterpart to the local ntuple validation job.

jobs/dev/numi_fhc_run1_dev.xml
     Grid job template for the dev imaging and inference chain.


3. Run local jobs
-----------------

The most common command form is:

     lar -c <fhicl_file> -s <input.root>

Examples:

     lar -c jobs/run_nuselection.fcl -s reco_input.root

     lar -c jobs/run_nuselection_data.fcl -s data_input.root

     lar -c jobs/run_nuselection_slim.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c jobs/run_nuselection_data_slim.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c jobs/run_imageprod.fcl -s reco_input.root

     lar -c jobs/run_inferenceprod.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c jobs/run_fullchain.fcl -s reco_input.root

Usage notes:

  * Use run_nuselection.fcl when you want flat analysis trees from MC-like
    input.
  * Use run_nuselection_data.fcl for data or EXT workflows when inference is available.
  * Use the `*_slim` selection jobs on input that contains
    `imageprod:CroppedWindow` and `imageprod:FullWindow` products when you do
    not want to run or depend on `inferenceprod`.
  * Use run_imageprod.fcl when you want persisted image products in the art
    event output.
  * Use run_inferenceprod.fcl only on input files that already contain the
    imageprod:CroppedWindow products expected by the InferenceProducer.
  * Use run_fullchain.fcl when starting from reconstructed input and you want
    the image, inference, and selection stages in one step.

For quick staged-workflow tests from this checkout, `.local.sh` now supports
either a SAM-backed mini-run or a direct local handoff between stages. It also
resolves bare FHiCL names from `FHICL_FILE_PATH`, so you can use the upstream
redk2nu/EventWeight entry points directly:

     SAM_DEF=prodgenie_numi_uboone_overlay_fhc_mcc9_run1_v28_v2_sample0 \
       ./.local.sh run_redk2nu_fhc.fcl 1

     ./.local.sh run_eventweight_microboone_sept24_numi_fhc.fcl \
       /absolute/path/to/previous_stage.root

     ./.local.sh run_imageprod.fcl \
       /absolute/path/to/previous_stage.root

When you pass an integer as the second argument, `.local.sh` resolves that many
files from `SAM_DEF`.  When you pass a `.root` path as the second argument, it
uses that file directly.  Outputs are written under `out/` by default.
Histogram outputs are combined automatically; art event outputs are left as
per-file ROOT files and are also listed in a `*_events.list` manifest so they
can be fed into the next stage.

For a compact local ntuple validation file, run the dedicated local ntuple
job on a single SAM file:

     SAM_DEF=prodgenie_numi_uboone_overlay_fhc_mcc9_run1_v28_v2_sample0 \
       ./.local.sh jobs/dev/flux/run_local_ntuple_dev.fcl 1

That produces one combined TFileService ROOT file under `out/`.
Because downstream ntuple consumers use the EventSelectionFilter and SubRun
trees, this selection-ntuple output is the intended local-test surface rather
than a full art event file.

If you want one wrapper that runs the checked-in dev chain end-to-end before
submitting a campaign, use:

     ./scripts/validate-campaign.sh --workflow mc

That defaults to the Run 1 FHC staged MC path:

  * `run_redk2nu_fhc.fcl`
  * `run_eventweight_microboone_sept24_numi_fhc.fcl`
  * `run_imageprod.fcl`
  * `jobs/dev/run_stage_sel_dev.fcl`

and enforces a single-file starting point so the local stage handoff stays on
one ROOT file at a time. You can switch workflows or inputs, for example:

     ./scripts/validate-campaign.sh --workflow data


     ./scripts/validate-campaign.sh --workflow ntuple

     ./scripts/validate-campaign.sh \
       --workflow mc \
       --evtw-config extragenie1 \
       --samdef prodgenie_numi_uboone_overlay_fhc_mcc9_run1_v28_sample1

The inference jobs expect the checked-in runtime bundle under runtime/,
including runtime/models/mink_binary/checkpoint_step0010000.pt and the wrapper
script reached through the RuntimeBaseDir setting.

When you want to run the same network architecture with multiple checkpoints,
put the shared settings in ModelDefaults and vary only the per-model labels and
Checkpoint values:

     ModelDefaults: {
       Arch: "binary:device=cpu,seed=12345,thr=0.0,in_ch=3"
       WeightsDir: "models/mink_binary"
     }
     Models: [
       { Label: "mink_binary_step0010000" Checkpoint: "checkpoint_step0010000.pt" }
       { Label: "mink_binary_step0020000" Checkpoint: "checkpoint_step0020000.pt" }
     ]


4. Run over SAM definitions
---------------------------

For quick local tests, a common pattern is to resolve a few files from a SAM
definition and loop over them:

     files=$(samweb list-files defname:<sam_definition> | head -n 3)

     counter=1
     for file in $files; do
         filedir=$(samweb locate-file "$file" | grep -o '/pnfs/.*' | head -n 1)
         lar -c jobs/run_fullchain.fcl -s "${filedir}/${file}"
         mv fullchain_nuselection_hist.root "fullchain_${counter}.root"
         counter=$((counter + 1))
     done

     hadd -f combined_fullchain.root fullchain_*.root

If you need to prepare or inspect SAM definitions, use the helper scripts in
scripts/ and the top-level describe-definitions.sh helper:

     ./scripts/train-template-pair.sh <source_def> <training_shard_def> <template_shard_def>

     ./scripts/campaign-jobs.sh

     ./scripts/train-template.sh --dry-run

     ./describe-definitions.sh

scripts/README.md records the current staged campaign surface, the source SAM
definitions behind it, and the Run 1 CV train/template shard strategy.


5. Understand the outputs
-------------------------

The package writes two kinds of ROOT output.

art event files
     These are written by jobs such as run_imageprod.fcl, run_inferenceprod.fcl,
     run_fullchain.fcl, run_fullchain_slim.fcl, and the extra-GENIE weight
     job.  They contain event
     products such as image::ImageFeatures and inference products.

TFileService analysis files
     These are files such as nu_selection.root, nu_selection_data.root, and
     fullchain_nuselection_hist.root.  They contain TTrees and analysis
     branches intended for downstream plotting and ntuple-style analysis.

The checked-in branch and product layout is summarized here.  In particular:

  * EventSelectionFilter trees live in nu_selection.root,
    nu_selection_data.root, fullchain_nuselection_hist.root,
    imaging_dev.root, and imaging_dev_cosmic.root.
  * ImageProducer writes the neutrino-centered sparse planes to
    imageprod:CroppedWindow and the detector-wide sparse planes to
    imageprod:FullWindow.
  * The image-only and inference-only histogram files are mainly framework
    side outputs; the repo-defined payload for those workflows is in the art
    event file.


6. Submit grid jobs
-------------------

`xml/` now contains these staged campaign entry points:

  * xml/numi_run1aot_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run1_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run1_rhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run2b_rhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run3b_rhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run4a_rhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run4b_rhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run4c_fhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run4d_fhc_campaign.xml
  * xml/numi_run5_fhc_campaign.xml

Older XMLs were archived under `reference/legacy_xml/`.

The campaign XMLs use the same building blocks:

  * MC beam, dirt, and dedicated strangeness stages use
    `redk2nu -> evtw -> image -> sel`
  * only `fcl_evtw_00` is active, so MC keeps the first 100 multisim
    universes
  * data and EXT stages use `image -> sel`
  * detector-variation chains, where present, use `image -> sel`
  * inference is omitted because the checked-in model bundle has not been
    updated yet
  * `numjobs` values are placeholders and should be replaced from `samweb`
    counts before submission

Run-specific notes:

  * Run 1 FHC includes the nominal beam/dirt shards, the dedicated
    strangeness sample, generic beam detvars, confirmed dedicated strangeness
    detvars, and explicit CV `train_shard` / `template_shard` stage families.
  * Run 2a FHC includes the nominal beam/dirt/strangeness chains plus the
    generic Run 2a FHC beam detvars.
  * Run 2b RHC includes the regenerated nominal beam chain, the Run 2 RHC
    dirt and strangeness chains, and the generic Run 2b RHC beam detvars.
  * Run 3b RHC includes the nominal beam and dirt shards, the Run 3 RHC
    strangeness chain, and the generic Run 3b RHC beam detvars.

Before submitting:

  * review the XML entities near the top of the file you plan to use
  * confirm the release tag, PNFS paths, and SAM definitions
  * replace the placeholder `numjobs` values with
    `samweb count-files defname:<...>` results
  * refresh the tarball with `./.tar.sh`

Run 1 CV train/template shards are created upstream at the SAM-definition
level. To build the checked-in shard names, run:

     ./scripts/train-template-pair.sh --batch scripts/run1-fhc-cv.plan

or use the wrapper:

     ./scripts/train-template.sh

The wrapper now caps only the training shard at roughly 100000 events by
default.
Use:

     ./scripts/train-template.sh --full-shards

when you want the original full alternating-file split instead.

To decide whether a source definition should be split first, query the file
counts from the active XMLs:

     ./scripts/campaign-jobs.sh

That helper uses a default sharding threshold of 5000 files, matching the
common NuMI note examples for splitting large SAM definitions with
`limit 5000` / `offset 5000`.

Nominal Run 1 submission example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_sel --submit

Run 1 CV train-shard detvar example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_detvar_cv_train_shard_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_detvar_cv_train_shard_image --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_detvar_cv_train_shard_sel --submit

Run 2a nominal example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_evtw --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_evtw --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_sel --submit

Run 2b nominal example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run2b_rhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_evtw --submit

Run 3b nominal example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run3b_rhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --submit

Stage naming follows a fixed pattern:

  * nominal shard-based campaigns use names such as `beam_shard0_evtw`,
    `beam_shard0_image`, `beam_shard0_sel`
  * unsplit nominal campaigns use names such as `beam_evtw`, `beam_image`,
    `beam_sel`
  * detvars use names such as `beam_detvar_sce_image`, `beam_detvar_sce_sel`
  * Run 1 dedicated strangeness detvars use names such as
    `strangeness_detvar_ly_rayleigh_image` and
    `strangeness_detvar_ly_rayleigh_sel`
  * Run 1 CV split chains use names such as
    `beam_detvar_cv_train_shard_image`,
    `beam_detvar_cv_template_shard_image`,
    `strangeness_detvar_cv_train_shard_image`, and
    `strangeness_detvar_cv_template_shard_image`

To clean and resubmit a stage, target the specific staged node you want to rerun:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --clean
     project.py --xml xml/numi_run1_fhc_campaign.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --submit


7. Common adjustments
---------------------

The checked-in job files are meant to be copied or overridden for your local
campaign.  Common edits include:

  * switching between MC and data by choosing the right top-level FHiCL file;
  * changing TFileService output names;
  * changing the inference model family, checkpoint, or wrapper path;
  * adjusting XML entities to point at your own PNFS areas and SAM inputs.

For development work, put ad hoc configurations under jobs/dev/ rather than editing
the production files in jobs/ without a reason.


8. If something fails early
---------------------------

Check the following first:

  * If lar cannot find included FHiCL files or products, your MRB setup is not
    complete.  Re-run source .setup.sh or the equivalent manual setup.
  * If samweb is missing, set up sam_web_client or use the helper setup script.
  * If an inference job fails immediately, confirm that you are running from
    the repository top directory and that
    runtime/models/mink_binary/checkpoint_step0010000.pt is present.
  * If a grid stage points to the wrong storage area, edit the entities in
    the XML file you are submitting before launching jobs.


End
